main event: Two round white objects were observed in the Pacific at 0145Z on September 3, 1961.
interesting points: The objects appeared about 30 minutes apart., The sighting lasted approximately 2-3 minutes., Observations were recorded via Ground-Radar., Comments suggested the objects might have been meteors in reflection., The report was submitted to the Department of the Air Force.
witness description: members of the Department of the Air Force
